train.text: Utterance: Hello I need a lot of water to survive , Label: self-need
Utterance: I have a lot of water around me I can use. So I can give you a lot of extra. , Label: no-need
Utterance: Ok nice I will give you 3 food if you give me 3 water , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: OK, that works for me. But I would like a lot of firewood. I like to hunt and cook what I kill. , Label: self-need
Utterance: Ok I will give you 2 firewood  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: So I get 3 food and 2 firewood? And you get all of the water? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: yes does that sound good to you? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Yes, I am happy with that arrangement.  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Alright so let us finalize , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Great, I hope your camping trip goes well!🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hi, how are you?  , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Am fine what about you? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Good thanks! So I'm hoping I can get all of the Food, but am willing to negotiate on the other items.  , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Ohh food?.Thats a very essential property over here.I mean very important.Do you really need it that bad? , Label: uv-part
Utterance: It's my top priority, but if you need some, I'd need more water and firewood , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: It aslo my top priority but i would not if u give me 3 packages of water and  2 firewood in exchange for all food.Agree? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: sure that works , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Okay deal sealed? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: yea good with me. 3 food 1 firewood for me. 3 water and 2 firewood for you , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: ok deal , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: hi, how are you? my main need is water. how bout you? , Label: small-talk,self-need,elicit-pref

Utterance: Hey hi, nice getting to interact with you. I'm doing good, thank you. Wish it's the same with you. I get dehydrated quickly and need additional packages of water. , Label: small-talk,self-need
Utterance: we both have the same high value priority. what is number 2 for you? thanks , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: 🙂 Food , Label: non-strategic

Utterance: me 2 lol, what if you got 2 of the water and me 1 but then i could do 2 of the food and firewood and things would kind of even out with that arrangement. , Label: promote-coordination,vouch-fair
Utterance: Yes, that would be fair. How much of Firewood would you need? , Label: vouch-fair,elicit-pref
Utterance: 2 firewood and 2 food and 1 water. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I get it as you need more firewood for the additional package of food. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: exactly, and forgot some of my extra wood at the house again. , Label: self-need
Utterance: Have a nice camping trip 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: you as well , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hi there! Curious as to what's on your mind regarding each item. I have my own preferences, but will share after you. , Label: promote-coordination,elicit-pref
Utterance: Hello, well I really need food. Have a lot of extra people. , Label: other-need
Utterance: Awesome - same, I also need a ton of food. Will firewood be of interest to you as well? I'll be happy to compensate in this way , Label: elicit-pref,promote-coordination
Utterance: Firewood is not overly interesting to me, but water is somewhat enticing. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Ok, great - I can give you all of my waters in exchange for a majority of the food and half of firewood , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Half of firewood? There are 3 so one of us has to get more. I would need more of that.  , Label: non-strategic

Utterance: Yep, I know there's three and no way to split evenly lol - can you give me a justifiable reason as to why you deserve more over me? Please convince me. , Label: promote-coordination,vouch-fair,elicit-pref
Utterance: Well, food is the most important and you're getting that so I'm gonna need more of the others. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: What are your thoughts on the amount of water you need? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: I would need 2 out of 3 as well. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Interesting - you're essentially saying that you need the majority of two of the three items. Hmm... , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Yes, thats all. I need 1/3 food, 2/3 water, and 2/3 firewood. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Still not convinced in any way that you need more items in total over me. Please clarify! , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Food is what I prioritize much more than the others. If you want the majority of the others, I will need all the food. , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Ok, I'm willing to compromise to speed this up - I'll go with the original plan you've outlined, and I'll take 2/3 food, 1/3 water, and 1/3 firewood , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Hello, how are you today? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: hello, I am good, I am very excited about this trip. how are you? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: i am great, super excited about camping as well, are there any supplies that you really need? , Label: small-talk,elicit-pref
Utterance: i really need water and food. we did not get enough of those. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: Those are my priorities as well, how about you get all the food and two firewoods, and i get all the water and one firewood, does that sound fair? , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: i would prefer water instead of food if possible, but i am sure we can work it out. , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: water is really important for me, how about i get two waters and three firewoods and you get three foods and one water? , Label: self-need
Utterance: i can work with 1 water 3 food and 1 firewood , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: ok that works for me , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: good, we used all the water to fix overheated car. , Label: self-need
Utterance: Hello, I'd like to get all of the water, an extra firewood and 2 of the food , Label: non-strategic

Utterance: Hi there.  That hardly leaves me with anything and doesn't really work for me.  I was hoping to make a campsite feast and get the extra food.  If we can do that, I'd be happy to give you all the water and that extra firewood. , Label: vouch-fair,self-need,promote-coordination
Utterance: I am a big guy, so I will need some more food, how about you give me an extra food while you hold on to two , Label: self-need

Utterance: I can't give you all the water if you take one of the food, I'm very sorry.  I could take 2 of the food and 2 of the water if we do it that way.  I really need cooking supplies if I want this trip to be productive for me - it's why I was coming. , Label: vouch-fair,self-need
Utterance: That wouldn't work for me, I will be going hiking during camping, so I need all of the water I can get , Label: vouch-fair

Utterance: Well then maybe we can just do a trade, the water to you and the food to me.  And if I got two of the firewood, I'd have plenty of time to just boil and purify some riverwater instead , Label: promote-coordination,no-need
Utterance: That does not seem entirely fare but I need more water so I will take this deal , Label: vouch-fair

Utterance: It's honestly not that fair to me either, but sometimes we just end up with slightly conflicting priorities in life.  🙂  I think making the best of the situation is the way forward. , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Yeah, That's true,🙂, so do we have a deal? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Yup, the food to me, the water to you, and 2 of the firewood to me, 1 to you is as I understand it! , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That's correct, a deal it is then , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Hello , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: HI how are you today? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Good. I am diabetic so would like to take 3 of the food , Label: self-need
Utterance: I would do that but our meat spoiled because the ice box was not properly closed. How about you get 2 of the meat, and I get 3 of the water? , Label: self-need
Utterance: ok I will just be able to get by with 2 of the food, I can give you all 3 of the water if I can take 2 of the wood. I have panic attacks in the dark. , Label: self-need
Utterance: Okay that works for me as well. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: awesome any chance I could persuade you to substitute your 1 food item for an additional fire wood 🙂 , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: No I cannot do that unfortunately. We brought just enough food for our weekend trip, and I cannot lose any or we will run out before our camping trip is over. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: OK, just thought I'd ask, so are we settled on you getting 1 Food, 1 firewood and 3 waters? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Yes that sounds like it will work for me. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Great. Have a good day , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hey there! I'm assuming you enjoy going camping? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Yes I do, I am going this weekend. Are you going camping too? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Same! I try to go every other weekend. , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Oh cool. What supplies do you prefer to take the most of? , Label: small-talk,elicit-pref
Utterance: I do a lot of hiking mostly, love to take scenic photos. I usually carry food and water supplies? , Label: self-need,small-talk
Utterance: Me too. I am not good at hunting or fishing. So I generally try to take extra food , Label: small-talk,self-need
Utterance: Haha I suck at those activities as well. I don't usually don't eat a lot, so I'm happy to exchange some food supplies for water supplies.  , Label: no-need,small-talk,promote-coordination
Utterance: I would be willing to do that. What do you propose? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: I get 2 water, 1 food and 1 firewood, you get 1 water, 2 food and 2 firewood.  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: You know what that sounds extremely fair. I would accept that offer , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: How's it going?  If it's alright with you, you can have all of the water and I'll take all of the firewood.  We can work out a deal on the food as well. , Label: promote-coordination

Utterance: I have circulatory issued due to a heart condition and cold quickly. I would appreciate if I could get at least 2 of the firewood. You can have 2 of the food so you won't get hungry. 🙂 , Label: self-need

Utterance: I was planning on building a big bonfire for the evening.  There'd be plenty of room if you wanted to join for warmth.  I'm a bit hungry and would appreciate the extra food.  You can have all of the water if you'd like.  If you warm it by the bonfire, it may be useful to soak in to improve your circulation. , Label: self-need,small-talk,uv-part

Utterance: I get tired to easy so I probably won't be much fun at a bonfire ☹️. I really do appreciate the offer though. I would think the extra food would do you more good for your party.  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: The extra food would be appreciated.  How about if I take just two each of the firewood and food, and you can have the remainder, plus all of the water? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I am just concerned that only 1 firewood might make it so I'm too cold to function.  , Label: non-strategic

Utterance: If you boil the water above the fire, it will provide additional heat over time.  You would also be able to make tea, which would warm you up from the inside as well, better than any fire would.  That would probably be most beneficial to you.  I really do need the 2 firewood if there's any chance of making a bonfire for my party. , Label: uv-part,other-need,self-need
Utterance: I am allergic to tea and coffee. I wonder if the smaller fire would be more quaint for everyone to sit around.  , Label: uv-part

Utterance: It really wouldn't do the job that well at all.  You could always prepare hot cocoa or use your share of the food to make a warm stew.  I really do need at least the two firewood and a couple of food.  You can have all the water to make a hearty and hot stew to get your through the night, though. , Label: uv-part

Utterance: I can't eat much anyway because of the health issues. You could have all of the food if I could get the extra firewood. That would still give you an extra firewood in addition to the basic supply and lots of extra food for your party. I'm sure they would love having some of the stew you mentioned. , Label: promote-coordination,uv-part
Utterance: Well, how about I take just the one extra firewood, plus all of the food, and one of the water so that I can make stew?  Would that work for you? , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: That sounds good. I hope your party is wonderful. , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hello there 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hello, I hope we can work together on an offer that benefits both of us. Do you think it's OK?🙂 , Label: promote-coordination,vouch-fair
Utterance: Yes definitely!  I am pretty easy to work with and would like a deal that will help us both out as much as possible. , Label: promote-coordination,vouch-fair
Utterance:  The item I need the most is water because I need to hydrate to stay strong and achieve my goals. And you? , Label: self-need,elicit-pref

Utterance: I would say water as well because I am very active and build up thirst as a result.  However, I would be willing to compromise on things to allow you to have more water. , Label: self-need,promote-coordination
Utterance: The item that I need the least is firewood because I will dedicate myself to look it up at the camp. And you? , Label: no-need,elicit-pref
Utterance: Yes I think we have the same preferences.  I do not get cold easily and will bring a heavy sleeping bag.   , Label: no-need
Utterance: Ok, it gets a little complicated. But let's see what you think if I grab: 3 water 1 food and 0 firewood? And you would take: 0 of water, 2 of food and 3 of firewood , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That is not a bad offer.  However, I would like at least 1 water for myself.  I would be willing to allow you 2 of the 3 waters though. , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Ok what do you think then if I give you 1 more water and you give me 1 more firewood. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That is quite fair.  I would agree to that :)  Should we go ahead and submit it? , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Hi! How is your camping trip going? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: It's going good we could use some more supplies such as food and firewood, though. , Label: small-talk,self-need,other-need
Utterance: Same here haha. Is water your lowest priority item too? , Label: small-talk,elicit-pref
Utterance: Yes. We think we have enough water for now. , Label: no-need
Utterance: Same here! I am in need of food more than firewood however as I am very hungry.  , Label: self-need
Utterance: Me too. We have a bigger family and we will run out of food if we don't get some more. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: Since it looks like we have the same value ranking for our needs, how would you like to try to make the deal? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Well let's try to make this as fair as possible.🙂We could get 2 packages of food, leaving you with 2 extra packages of firewood as well as water. , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Sounds great to me! So I will get 1 food, 2 firewood, and 2 water. That sounds very fair 🙂 , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Yes. I'm glad we were able to come to an agreement so fast. This is great!🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hi, how are you? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I am doing very well. Have you planned your camping trip? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: A bit and you? I'm looking forward to figuring out a deal that helps us both! , Label: small-talk
Utterance: That's great. 🙂 We are planning to prepare food over a fire. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: Nice! What are your highest priority items? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: We need a moderate amount of everything and I think we can work something out successfully. , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: got it, OK I'll start then. I'd like at least 2 firewood , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Okay. we brought some of our own food so I don't need much of that either. , Label: no-need
Utterance: do you want more water then? perhaps 2? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: Yes 🙂  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: ok great. I think I can do that, I'd like to have 2 food then if you're OK with that , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Hi, I would like two firewoods and two food. You can take everything else. Does that work for you? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That might work. What reasons do you have for needing those? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: I want to make smores and a nice dinner , Label: self-need
Utterance: I feel like I might need more firewood, I'm staying in the desert and it gets cold at night. , Label: self-need
Utterance: I could do one firewood and all the food? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: And I would get all the water? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: How about you get two firewoods and two water, and I take the rest? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: No I think I need all the water. I'm in the desert and there's absolutely no water supply.  , Label: self-need
Utterance: so you want two firewoods and three waters and I get everything else?  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That sounds good to me! , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I really need at least two firewoods to cook with though, or one water. How can we make this work? , Label: self-need
Utterance: I could give you two firewood, if I could still have my three waters and then 1 food. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Okay lets do that.  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I need some firewood because I did not bring enough, I was thinking I could take 2 firewood, 1 food, and 2 water. What do you think? , Label: self-need
Utterance: I can do that for you! , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Ok, so you must prefer water and food over firewood. We might have lucked out as far as our priorities go!🙂 , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Yes pretty much that sounds like we can work something out , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Would you be willing to let me have all the firewood and you could take 2 of the food and 2 of the water? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: No I can't do that unfortunately./ , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Ok, so I could take 2 firewood, 1 food, and 1 water, the original deal, do you still want to do that one? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I would prefer the original deal , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Ok, I am good with the original deal also.  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That sounds good to me. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: Hello, how are you today? 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: good, how are you 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Great!  I'm on a camping trip with my five children, how about you? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I'm also going camping with my two children and 2 of my nephews  How would you like to divide the supplies? , Label: small-talk,promote-coordination
Utterance: Well what do you need the most of? , Label: elicit-pref

Utterance: I need the most firewood due to a congenital issue that results in us having poor blood circulation to our extremities, thus making them susceptible to frostbite in the cold! , Label: self-need,other-need

Utterance: Oh dear, that sounds serious!  Well I need food the most because my children eat sooo much and I don't think I packed enough.  How about I'll give you all my firewood in exchange for all your food? , Label: showing-empathy,other-need,promote-coordination
Utterance: Would you be down for an arrangement where I get 2 wood, I get 1 food, and 1 water? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Sure that sounds good!  I hope you have a nice trip! , Label: small-talk
Utterance: you too! , Label: small-talk

Utterance: Hi there.. we're looking forward to this camping trip.. hope you are, too!  Is there anything in particular you guys need / want out of the extra stockpile we've got? , Label: small-talk,elicit-pref
Utterance: Hello! Which item do you need the most? , Label: elicit-pref

Utterance: Well we actually really NEED all three items.. but I know you might, too - so I want to make a deal that's fair for you.. is there anything in particular your family needs for the trip? , Label: self-need,other-need,vouch-fair,elicit-pref
Utterance: Well, there has to be an item that you need the most. If you tell me what you need the most, we can try to make a deal around it. , Label: elicit-pref

Utterance: Oh I see, its going to be THAT kind of negotiation 🙂  Let's just look at it this way.. I'm with a couple other Floridians so we're not really too worried about firewood as we prefer it cooler, anyway.. and we know the lake is nearby that's stocked with trout for eating if necessary (and of course some fresh water's there, too) - so.. I can tell you that I could go totally without Firewood if I needed to.. I'd rather not, but I could. , Label: no-need
Utterance: Do you prefer food or water more? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: Since the lake is nearby enough, I think we'd be more interested in ensuring there's enough food for my people, I think 🙂 , Label: self-need,no-need,other-need
Utterance: Hmm. I really need food too. I don't care much for water either. How about I take all 3 firewood, 2 food, and 1 water? , Label: self-need,no-need

Utterance: Yeah, that's not going to work for me.. I can give you two food if you really need it, but in exchange I'm going to need two of the water and all the firewood.   , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: I will just take 3 firewood, 1 food, and 1 water. That work for you? , Label: non-strategic

Utterance: Tell you what.. now that I think about it.. you seem like you really need the firewood.. no problem.  I want you to have all 3 of them.. and you can have 1 water and 1 food, too.. does that work for you?  That would just leave me 2 food, 2 water, and no firewood. , Label: showing-empathy
Utterance: Hi! Which items are important to you? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: Food is the most important to me because I need to eat more often so that I can take my medications.   , Label: self-need
Utterance: Yeah, that is important. I do not have a problem letting you have more food than me. , Label: showing-empathy
Utterance: Would it be possible to get an extra water also?  How do you feel about the firewood?  I wish we could split everything evenly.🙂 , Label: elicit-pref,vouch-fair
Utterance: Me too. Firewood is the most important thing to me. We will be somewhere cold and we could use the extra warmth. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: True.  How about I get 2 food, 2 water and 1 firewood. And that will leave you with 2 firewood, 1 water, and 1 food?  , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: What do you need the extra water for? , Label: elicit-pref
Utterance: With the extra food I need I will need extra water also.  How about I only take 1 extra water?   , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: So are you okay with you getting 2 food, 1 water, and 1 firewood and me getting 1 food, 2 water and 2 firewood? I'll do that deal. , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: That should work.  I will conserve with my water and I should be fine.  So we have a deal?   , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hi there. Have you ever been camping? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I have, i love camping! How about you? , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I have not, but I don't really have an interest for it, either. , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Thats a shame, i am sure you would like it if you give it a try, especially if you build a large fire 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I was going to say, the fire would be probably one of the few things I would be interested in! I love being warm. , Label: self-need
Utterance: Well you can take all the firewood if it will help, would it be ok if i get all the food in return? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: That works for me. How would you like to divide the water? , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: I am ok with you taking two waters since you are new to camping, does that seem fair to you? , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: Yes, that seems fair to me. , Label: vouch-fair
Utterance: So you get 3 firewoods and two waters and i get 3 foods and one water, deal? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: we have a deal! great speaking with you today 🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hello. I am so looking forward to this camp out. My daughter just called and said she is going to come and bring some of her firiends. 🙂 , Label: small-talk,self-need

Utterance: Hello! That sounds pretty reasonable to me. I was going out with a bunch of my buddies. We like to hike a lot in the sun, so we need lots of water. How does it sound if i take all the food and water, but you get all the firewood? , Label: showing-empathy,small-talk,self-need,other-need

Utterance: I love hiking. My daughter is bringing extra water. So we could trade the water for the firewood. We do need just a little food as I didn't plan on having an extra person. , Label: promote-coordination,no-need,other-need
Utterance: Hmm, okay, that sounds reasonable. How does 3 water, 2 food and 1 firewood for me, and all the rest for you sound? , Label: showing-empathy

Utterance: Im goign to need all the firewood I can get. They want to cook smores on it. How about you get 3 water 2 food and I get 3 firewood and 1 food. I think that is very fair and would help us both out. 🙂🙂 , Label: self-need,vouch-fair

Utterance: That sounds like a very reasonable deal, I understand how girls can get with their snacks haha. I'm okay with giving up all the firewood. You said you need at least some of the food, right? , Label: showing-empathy
Utterance: Thanks. Yea they do  love their snacks LOL. Yea I just need 1 extra food. Snice I wasn't planning on her friend coming.  , Label: other-need
Utterance: Okay, then the deal you mentioned earlier sounds good to me. You're okay with me getting 3 water 2 food and you getting 3 firewood and 1 food? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: 🙂 Yep sounds like it will help us out the best snice you need water and food for your hike and I need firewood and just 1 food here at the camp. , Label: promote-coordination
Utterance: Okay, then that sounds like a good deal for us both! It was a pleasure doing business with you, thanks!🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: Hello. I am so looking forward to this camp out with my son. What bring you out to the camp?🙂 , Label: small-talk
Utterance: I love the outdoors, and I am excited to spend time with everyone from camp. It's been since last year when I saw everyone! , Label: small-talk
Utterance: That's awesome! I really love being out here with my son. Do you think you could spare some Food and Firewood? I have plenty of water if you need some. , Label: small-talk

Utterance: I am actually planning to make a big dinner for the whole camp tonight. I will feed everyone if you can let me have the water and firewood. You can take the food to eat before dinner. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: O cool🙂. I can give you all the water and we can split the fire wood. I need a least one firewood to make a fire for my son , Label: showing-empathy,other-need
Utterance: I can give you one firewood if you can spare one food for me to eat while I am cooking.🙂 , Label: self-need
Utterance: Ok if I can keep one water as well 🙂 , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I may not be able to go without the water. I am making a large pot of soup with homemade bread. , Label: self-need,other-need
Utterance: 😮 This is not looking good. I think we are close but I really need that one water for my son. , Label: other-need
Utterance: If I can give you one of the waters, will you make a deal with me? , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: I will need 2 firewoods for cooking tonight , Label: self-need
Utterance: ok 🙂 , Label: non-strategic
Utterance: What are your preferences?  I always love having a big fire at night when I am camping and I do think water is more important than food. , Label: elicit-pref,self-need
